    "body": "I believe nargs to vectorcall is taken as fact, and it doesn't generally handle `NULL` values as part of the array.\r\n\r\nTargeted at 3.2.x because I have a slightly bigger change aimed at 3.3 which includes the same fix.",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-12T13:52:28Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7677#discussion_r3226930818"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/cython/cython/pulls/7677"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/cython/cython/pulls/comments/3226930818"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I was wondering if this is safe or if `val` could be `NULL` without `tb` being `NULL`, so I looked through the usages and found that all usages of `__Pyx__Coroutine_Throw()` are directly or indirectly preceded by a call to `PyArg_UnpackTuple()` to get the exception info, which unpacks left-to-right.\n\nLooks good then.",
            "commit_id": "3fac4cf1d72565668ccf8b988ab9854f70c91e90",
            "created_at": "2026-05-12T13:51:14Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -1311,9 +1311,10 @@ static PyObject *__Pyx__Coroutine_Throw(PyObject *self, PyObject *typ, PyObject\n             if (likely(args)) {\n                 ret = __Pyx_PyObject_Call(meth, args, NULL);\n             } else {\n-                // \"tb\" or even \"val\" might be NULL, but that also correctly terminates the argument list\n+                // \"tb\" or even \"val\" might be NULL.\n                 PyObject *cargs[4] = {NULL, typ, val, tb};\n-                ret = __Pyx_PyObject_FastCall(meth, cargs+1, 3 | __Pyx_PY_VECTORCALL_ARGUMENTS_OFFSET);\n+                Py_ssize_t nargs = 1 + (val != NULL) + (tb != NULL);\n+                ret = __Pyx_PyObject_FastCall(meth, cargs+1, nargs | __Pyx_PY_VECTORCALL_ARGUMENTS_OFFSET);",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7677#discussion_r3226930818",
            "id": 3226930818,
            "line": 1317,
            "node_id": "PRRC_kwDOABDGAc7AVw6C",
